275
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:57,480
- Can I have it?
- Hey. You said you'd pay for the whole tab.

276
00:28:57,873 --> 00:29:01,233
I'm transferring your fee right now.
It's enough to buy ten more cups.

277
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,120
I'm taking this.

278
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:05,280
Is that all you need?

279
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,520
Thank you.

280
00:29:29,547 --> 00:29:32,775
The guy talking to the owner
is Freeze. He's a dentist.

281
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:33,840
They've exchanged numbers.

282
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:36,480
You can see it from
Mars—he's hitting on him.

283
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:41,720
He made some excuse about
flyers just to ask him out.

284
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:54,840
Someone's hitting on your Mama today.

285
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:58,280
He's a dentist, no less.

286
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:07,600
Can your Dad even compete with that?

287
00:30:15,560 --> 00:30:17,240
Once we're done,

288
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:20,520
never show your face to me again.

289
00:30:21,680 --> 00:30:23,800
Not even as friends.

290
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:26,960
Remember what you just said!

291
00:30:43,193 --> 00:30:45,553
I'm rooting for this guy with all I've got.

292
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:54,440
Me too! He's polite, warm,
and has a stable career.

293
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:58,280
I'm sure he can take good care of you.

294
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:04,120
Enough, both of you.

295
00:31:04,320 --> 00:31:07,360
P'Freeze hasn't even done anything.

296
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:09,440
I know that right away,

297
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:13,280
that "using flyers
just to ask you out" move.

298
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:15,359
It's such a classic.

299
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:16,360
Oh.

300
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:18,216
You're way too naïve.

301
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:21,720
If he's not interested, he wouldn't
show up two days in a row like this.

302
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:26,040
Mark my words, he'll be back tomorrow.

303
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:33,120
He's just a customer stopping by for coffee.

304
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:38,040
There are hundreds of cafes
around here. Why specifically mine?

305
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:39,320
Am I right?

306
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:41,460
Exactly.

307
00:31:42,273 --> 00:31:44,673
You should open your heart a little.

308
00:31:50,232 --> 00:31:52,672
Or are you waiting for Jimmy?

309
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:03,640
What is it about Jimmy that
makes you head over heels for him?

310
00:32:04,906 --> 00:32:06,946
Alright, that's enough.

311
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,720
I'm going back to work.

312
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:41,000
I need to spend time with Mr. Freeze.

313
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:43,400
I'll ask to tutor him.

314
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:46,720
P'Toh will surely give in then.

315
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:50,320
More like give in to Jimmy
if he comes back to beg.

316
00:33:50,880 --> 00:33:54,760
No way. When P'Toh
says it's over, it's over.

317
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:57,520
He looks kind, but he can be very stubborn.

318
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:00,800
You might be right.

319
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:03,200
When I mentioned Jimmy earlier,

320
00:34:03,960 --> 00:34:05,360
he just shut me down.

321
00:34:05,840 --> 00:34:07,600
Maybe there's no return this time.

322
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:11,040
If that's true, I'll be so satisfied.

323
00:34:11,720 --> 00:34:15,000
I'm just waiting for the
day P'Toh dates Dr. Freeze.

324
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:17,320
I'll post a photo and
rub it in Jimmy's face!

325
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:21,840
You're pretty savage.

326
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:34,920
Plaifah!

327
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,040
P'Toh will see us.

328
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:39,960
Don't worry. It's kinda exciting.

329
00:34:46,160 --> 00:34:47,520
Don't be too loud, okay?

330
00:36:16,086 --> 00:36:17,806
It's too lonely to drink alone.

331
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,360
Wanna hang out with me?

332
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:22,960
No.

333
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:26,400
I have a boyfriend.

334
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:29,240
Oh, you have one?

335
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:34,760
But he broke up with me.

336
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:37,320
He's not coming back.

337
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:46,640
I have to fix this…

338
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:54,360
Then I hope you can win him back.

339
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:13,720
Stealing my girl like that?
You think you're hot?

340
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:17,600
You want some, punks?!

341
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:19,800
- Come at me!
- I'll get you.

342
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:38,560
So much for Mr. Hotshot.

343
00:39:12,913 --> 00:39:14,233
God, you're so damn huge.

344
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:17,040
And heavy as hell.

345
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:23,080
You'd better be grateful when you sober up.

346
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:37,920
P'Toh.

347
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:41,080
Did you see that?

348
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:44,520
I didn't go with another guy.

349
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:48,320
Am I a good boy?

350
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:50,960
Good boy, your ass!

351
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:54,720
You wouldn't hurt my brother
if you were actually good!

352
00:39:57,120 --> 00:39:58,640
Teh!

353
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:01,920
My best buddy.

354
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:10,120
Can you please tell your
brother that… I'm sorry?

355
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:13,160
I was wrong.

356
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:15,159
Please.

357
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:17,960
Too late for that. Serves you right.

358
00:40:19,040 --> 00:40:21,479
Move it, I'm taking you home.

359
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:23,440
I'm not going back!

360
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:27,760
I'm not going back!

361
00:40:30,920 --> 00:40:32,880
I want to beg P'Toh.

362
00:40:34,840 --> 00:40:37,000
Since I've broken up with him,

363
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:40,800
I've always missed him.

364
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:45,880
I miss him every single night.

365
00:40:48,560 --> 00:40:51,040
If I could've turned back time,

366
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:54,440
I would've done everything better.

367
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:58,880
I wouldn't have disappointed him.

368
00:41:09,240 --> 00:41:11,360
You must help me.

369
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:17,360
I'm begging you.

370
00:41:33,205 --> 00:41:34,265
Just get in the car.

371
00:41:44,200 --> 00:41:46,960
If I could've turned back time,

372
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:51,160
I wouldn't have loved you like this.

373
00:43:11,800 --> 00:43:13,760
P'Toh.

374
00:43:24,960 --> 00:43:26,400
P'Toh.

375
00:43:28,800 --> 00:43:32,720
I'm so sorry for bringing him here.

376
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:36,000
He was wasted.

377
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:39,000
And almost got his ass kicked.

378
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:45,160
When he wakes up, tell him to leave.
I don't want to see his face.

379
00:43:46,480 --> 00:43:48,400
P'Toh.

380
00:43:50,920 --> 00:43:54,440
I've never seen him this broken before.

381
00:44:01,800 --> 00:44:05,080
I'm going to bed.
I have to open the café early.

382
00:44:13,800 --> 00:44:18,480
If P'Toh is mad at me, you're dead, moron.

383
00:44:37,080 --> 00:44:38,600
P'Toh.

384
00:44:39,360 --> 00:44:40,640
Feeling better?

385
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:42,920
P'Toh.

386
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:45,480
I promise.

387
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:49,000
I won't hurt you ever again.

388
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:55,360
It's too late for that, Jimmy.

389
00:44:57,080 --> 00:44:59,639
P'Toh.

390
00:44:59,640 --> 00:45:01,520
P'Toh!

391
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:55,440
Well, your Mama started it.

392
00:46:57,760 --> 00:47:01,080
I'm not gonna die over something like this.

393
00:47:01,840 --> 00:47:03,120
We're through.

394
00:47:05,280 --> 00:47:08,360
I don't give a damn anyway.

395
00:47:29,040 --> 00:47:32,760
Mama hasn't stopped loving me, right?

396
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:56,440
(Next Episode) Please help
me get back with your brother.

397
00:47:58,760 --> 00:47:59,920
P'Toh!

398
00:48:00,680 --> 00:48:01,720
I'm so sorry.

399
00:48:02,480 --> 00:48:03,720
Please give me one more chance.

400
00:48:07,080 --> 00:48:08,480
I really like you.

401
00:48:09,640 --> 00:48:11,600
Would you like to try dating me?
